For various reasons, my unittest tests against installed packages and it took me a while to figure out why `monkeytype` does not record any type information. I ended up writing the following `monkeytype_config.py`

```
from types import CodeType
from monkeytype.tracing import CodeFilter
from monkeytype.config import DefaultConfig, default_code_filter

class MyConfig(DefaultConfig):

    def code_filter(self) -> CodeFilter:
        def my_code_filter(code: CodeType) -> bool:
            return 'mypackage' in code.co_filename or default_code_filter(code)
        return my_code_filter

CONFIG = MyConfig()
```
where `mypackage` is a hard-coded name for my pakcage. This works, but it is inconvenient when I try to trace different packages, so I am wondering if MonkeyType can provide a command line option to allow tracing certain packages in `site_packages`.

